The paper discusses the performance of HTTP-based video streaming, which involves network protocols and multimedia content. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes an adaptive algorithm for selecting the download size, which involves optimization and control theory, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another likely category. The paper also discusses the interaction between TCP congestion control and router queue occupancy, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a new video player called Sprint, which involves system design and implementation, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another possible category.
